http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Hyderabad/Former-Sikkim-Governor-Rama-Rao-laid-to-rest/article14005212.ece

The mortal remains of veteran Bharatiya Janata Party leader and former Sikkim Governor V. Rama Rao were consigned to flames at ‘Mahaprasthanam’ in Whisper Valley here on Monday afternoon.Among those present during the last journey of the soft-spoken, much-loved leader were Union Minister M. Venkaiah Naidu, former Chief Minister K. Rosaiah, former Ministers Nagam Janardhan Reddy and S. Santosh Reddy and State Secretary S. Prakash Reddy. As the flames leapt into the air, they paid their respects.Earlier in the morning, Governor E.S.L. Narasimhan and Chief Minister K. Chandrasekhar Rao were among those who drove over to Rama Rao’s residence and paid their respects. Later, the body of Rama Rao was kept in the Bharatiya Janata Party’s State office for people to have a last glimpse, before the last journey began.Other leaders who also came to the party office were Union Minister Nirmala Seetharaman, Suravaram Sudhakar Reddy, Chada Venkat Reddy, former MP Azeez Pasha and Manda Krishna Madiga. Among those who spent time with the family members since yesterday were the BJP’s National General Secretary Muralidhar Rao, Union Minister Bandaru Dattatareya, Telangana State President and MLA G. Kishan Reddy and the party’s Floor Leader in the State Assembly, K. Laxman.Rama Rao was said to be suffering from severe lung infection and hospitalised a month ago. He was a practising lawyer at the Andhrra Pradesh and elected as Member of the Legislative Council four times and was also imprisoned during the emergency. He served as President of the State unit of the party twice between 1992 and 1996 and worked as Governor of Sikkim too.